  "prompt": "Has any Modi supporter turned into a Kejriwal supporter?",
  "response": "Political affiliations can change over time, and it's not uncommon for individuals to switch their support from one political leader or party to another due to various reasons such as policy changes, personal experiences, or shifts in political landscape. There have been instances where individuals who initially supported Prime Minister Narendra Modi and the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) have expressed support for Arvind Kejriwal and the Aam Aadmi Party (AAP). \n\nFactors that might contribute to such changes include disillusionment with certain government policies, performance in governance, or the appeal of alternatives promised by Kejriwal and AAP, particularly in areas like education and healthcare in Delhi. Social media and public forums often showcase these shifts in support, as individuals share their experiences and opinions.\n\nHowever, specific cases or statistics on this kind of shift can be difficult to track, as political support can be highly personal and fluid.",
